Social Development Minister Lindiwe Zulu is to elaborate on the socio-economic relief interventions on COVID-19 Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Minister of Social Development Lindiwe Zulu elaborated on the socio-economic relief interventions on COVID-19. South Africa's COVID-19 cases are nearing 5,000 with 93 deaths. According to the Health Ministry, most COVID-19 deaths are as a result of underlying conditions.